Trump order turns federal land at us border into military installation
the u. s. Military will take control of a strip of federal land that spans three states along the southern border in an effort to stem illegal immigration, a memorandum Friday by Donald trump said.
The memorandum, " military mission for sealing the southern border of the United States and repelling invasions, " directs the secretaries of defense, interior, agriculture and homeland security" to provide for the use and jurisdiction by the department of defense over federal lands, including the Roosevelt reservation and excluding federal Indian reservations, that are reasonably necessary to enable military activities. "
He wrote it could include" border - barrier construction and emplacement of detection and monitoring equipment. "
